1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:04,000
In Vessel of Hatred, we travel south to Nahantu,

2
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:08,000
a region with both deep ancient jungles and vast sprawling plains.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:11,000
It's the last stretch of land in Sanctuary's eastern continent,

4
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,000
and we've packed it full of experiences for every type of player.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
In this expansion, there's a whole lot to explore under the dark canopy of Nahantu.

6
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Nahantu is the southernmost region of the eastern continent

7
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,000
that Diablo 4 has been taking place in.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:34,000
It's the last region that we haven't visited yet so far in the game,

9
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:37,000
but it is one that we've been to before in Diablo.

10
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,000
There's lots of new areas.

11
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:40,000
We have six in total.

12
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,000
Four of them are jungle-themed,

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,000
and then we have two that are Red Rock Canyon,

14
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
but each one of them has their own unique identity.

15
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:49,000
When you first arrive in Nahantu,

16
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,000
you're in this place called Lingering Hatred.

17
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:54,000
This is high treetops canopies

18
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:57,000
where you're almost walking amongst the branches high above the jungle floor.

19
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Imagine a thick canopy that the light is just barely poking through.

20
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:05,000
The whole area has been infected by this thing called the hollows infestation.

21
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
The hollows are a new enemy that's associated with Mephisto.

22
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
They themselves are kind of like a tar-like substance creature

23
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:13,000
born straight out of the depths of hell.

24
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,000
It feels a little twisted.

25
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:17,000
There's a sickness to the area itself.

26
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:21,000
Humans have ventured into this deep part of the jungle

27
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
where there's all this poisonous plants and flora.

28
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:28,000
The dregs actually started experimenting with eating these hallucinogens,

29
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
and it put them into this aggressive psycho rage.

30
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:36,000
The dregs were pretty fun because we were able to push more variety in the monster family.

31
00:01:36,000 --> 00:01:41,000
You have one of these tall dregs and then half of a body of another dreg on top of it

32
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:46,000
kind of controlling it and telling it where to go and tossing poisonous bombs at the player.

33
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:49,000
When you come across it, it's very memorable.

34
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:51,000
And then we've also got the area of Tenghansi

35
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
where you've got the Tenghansi Plateau,

36
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
which is full of these red rocked plateaus and canyons.

37
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
Imagine getting up above the land.

38
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:04,000
Those gigantic walls have pockets inside where monsters could live.

39
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:09,000
It offered up a lot of opportunity to bring back a monster family like the Lucunai.

40
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:14,000
We're bringing them back in a new way here as a fully fleshed out monster family with multiple classes.

41
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:18,000
What a more brute force looks like, what a caster looks like.

42
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:22,000
They are very much apex predators, and we're definitely in their territory.

43
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
And then there's a little sub area called the Skittering Earth.

44
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
The name alone makes your skin crawl.

45
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:34,000
It's bug infested, and you can see how the bugs have destroyed the jungles

46
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:36,000
and kind of input their influence on it.

47
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:41,000
Within the Field of Giants, you have these giant corpses of these long dead demons

48
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:45,000
that humans have begun to mine away at for their resources.

49
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
While they've got a lot of use out of them, they're also toxic to the land around it.

50
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:57,000
The notion of massive demons walking sanctuary a thousand years ago is really thought-provoking.

51
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,000
Plateau's also got just this beautiful color scheme to the lighting.

52
00:03:01,000 --> 00:03:03,000
It's really lovely to be there.

53
00:03:03,000 --> 00:03:05,000
And then horrific at the same time. You know, it's great.

54
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:13,000
The mercenaries in Vessel of Hatred are a group of people who we like to describe

55
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:15,000
as ordinary people with extraordinary skills.

56
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:20,000
They have the same level of will to fight against the demons of hell.

57
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:24,000
And there's four mercs that you can collect over the course of the campaign.

58
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:28,000
It starts with Rahir, a blacksmith and a shield bearer who's more defensive fighter.

59
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:34,000
He's able to go in there and soak up damage, use his shield as a bulwark against the enemy.

60
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Meet him early on in the campaign and he's one who introduces you to the mercenary network.

61
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:43,000
You end up finding acquisition quests for three other mercs that you can find throughout the course of the story.

62
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:50,000
Subo, the drunken archer, is going to work really well for people who want someone who's out of the main melee,

63
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:54,000
in the back, offering utility and that kind of range support.

64
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:59,000
Then we have Varyana, a berserker crone who's a melee combat fighter, close range.

65
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:05,000
You've got a really cool combat meter, a massacre meter where you need to keep killing enemies to get the meter to be filled.

66
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:09,000
She's got a bunch of really interesting utility skills that you can kind of build in.

67
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:17,000
Finally, we have the demon child, Aldkin, who's a magic user who can transform himself from human form to demon form and join you in combat.

68
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:23,000
There's this really great reinforcement ability where you can take one of the mercenary skills and attach it to one of the mercenary skills.

69
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:29,000
You can also use the skill of your powers so that when you use that skill, it calls them in to do a specific skill.

70
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:35,000
With the mercenaries for Vessel of Hatred, one of the things we are expanding on is the skill tree.

71
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:43,000
For Diablo III, you had a very basic type of mercenary, but this time you can actually push a little bit more into the skill tree

72
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,000
and make the mercenary the way you would want to play.

73
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:52,000
Going through each mercenary progression arc and outfitting their skill tree so that it's complementary to your character build,

74
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:55,000
I think that's where the fun in the mercenary system really lies.

75
00:04:55,000 --> 00:05:04,000
The Dark Citadel is a new in-game feature that's coming in Vessel of Hatred.

76
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:08,000
It's an entirely cooperative player experience.

77
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:17,000
All the mechanics within it are based around you working together with your party members to solve the challenges and face the first cars that are hordes within.

78
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:24,000
One of the outcomes of the Mage Wars is this giant crater and all the souls that were kind of lost in it from those wars.

79
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:38,000
The goal of the first Khazrah, who are kind of the original Khazrah, they're using the powers within the Citadel found within this crater to perform experiments to try and bring back their Dark God.

80
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:45,000
Only recently, people have started going missing. They head into the Khazrah region, they disappear, never to be seen again.

81
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:51,000
So it's clear that whatever they're planning is about to come to fruition and your job as the player is to get in there and stop it.

82
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:58,000
Citadel is a place where we take what is the best part of Diablo, combat, and we test it in a different way,

83
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:03,000
which is adding in cooperative mechanics that you have to manage on top of that.

84
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:09,000
For example, a boss has an attack, and as a player, you have to collect an item that allows you to reflect the attack back at him.

85
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:14,000
So there's a little bit of a twitch level mechanic there where you actually have to time your reaction shot.

86
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:19,000
What's interesting about it is when you get multiple people in there, we're each responsible for reflecting that shot once,

87
00:06:19,000 --> 00:06:22,000
so we all have to sort of master the timing of that move.

88
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:27,000
You can't do that kind of thing without coordinating as a team, and that's sort of the example of what Citadel gameplay feels like.

89
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:31,000
When designing the Citadel, we designed a lot of really cool bosses.

90
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:37,000
And so one of the things that we did is we took that design and made, like, armor sets for each of the classes.

91
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:43,000
That way you feel like you took their armor and you feel like you're wearing a little bit of them after your victory.

92
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:48,000
We also have a currency that's dedicated to Citadel where, as you play through,

93
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:53,000
a vendor can be interacted with to buy custom cosmetics that are unique to the Citadel.

94
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:57,000
You can play with two people, but the ideal experience is for four.

95
00:06:57,000 --> 00:07:01,000
In order to facilitate that, we've built an all-new Party Finder feature,

96
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:05,000
